$\S$ Using the above definition of equality, the empty set axiom, and the pairwise union axiom, prove that the following sets are distinct: $\phi, \{\phi\}, \{\{\phi\}\}, \{\phi, \{\phi\}\}$.

Hypothesis:

$$
  \begin{align}
    A = B \rightarrow (\forall x \in A, x \in B) \wedge (\forall x \in B, x \in A) \tag 1 \\
    \forall x, x \not\in \phi \tag 2 \\
    x \in A \cup B \leftrightarrow x \in A \vee x \in B \tag 3
  \end{align}
$$
